FBIS4-16780 "drsov076_b_94028" FBIS-SOV-94-076 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Favors Defense Spending Cut Favors Defense Spending Cut LD2004095294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004095294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Yegor Gaydar, leader of the parliamentary group Russia's Choice, believes the country's budget expenditure on defense should be cut. In an interview for DELOVOY MIR, he noted that 37 trillion rubles have been earmarked in the draft budget for military spending; in other words a fifth of the budget. Yegor Gaydar believes it necessary for the Russian Army to be tailored to the new conditions and new possibilities that exist in the country.
